    <item>
      <title>Runtime vs Environment</title>
      <link>http://localhost:3000/docs/managing-dependencies/runtime-vs-environment/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:3000/docs/managing-dependencies/runtime-vs-environment/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;FsFlow models dependencies by drawing a strict line between &lt;strong&gt;business dependencies&lt;/strong&gt; and &lt;strong&gt;operational services&lt;/strong&gt;. This is one of the defining architectural ideas of the library, inspired by the runtime model of ZIO.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;In FsFlow:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Business dependencies&lt;/strong&gt; (repositories, gateways, domain services) live in the &lt;strong&gt;Explicit Environment&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Operational services&lt;/strong&gt; (clock, logging, random numbers, scheduling) live in the &lt;strong&gt;Ambient Runtime&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Understanding &lt;em&gt;why&lt;/em&gt; this distinction exists is key to writing clean, maintainable workflows that scale without suffering from type-signature bloat.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Nominal Capability Contracts</title>
      <link>http://localhost:3000/docs/managing-dependencies/capability-contracts/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:3000/docs/managing-dependencies/capability-contracts/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;In FsFlow, the environment (&lt;code&gt;&#39;env&lt;/code&gt;) represents the &amp;ldquo;world&amp;rdquo; your effects need to run. Depending on the size of your application and your need for strictness, FsFlow provides three &amp;ldquo;levels&amp;rdquo; of environment access.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;level-1-records-the-pragmatic-way&#34;&gt;Level 1: Records (The Pragmatic Way)&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;For local logic or small applications, a plain F# record is often the best choice. It is direct, easy to mock, and requires zero ceremony.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h3 id=&#34;accessing-via-flowread&#34;&gt;Accessing via &lt;code&gt;Flow.read&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Use &lt;code&gt;Flow.read&lt;/code&gt; to project a specific property from your environment record.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Standard .NET AppHost Plus DI</title>
      <link>http://localhost:3000/docs/managing-dependencies/provider-edge/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:3000/docs/managing-dependencies/provider-edge/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;code&gt;IServiceProvider&lt;/code&gt; belongs at the outer edge of the system.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Using FsFlow with standard .NET Dependency Injection gives you:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Host registrations that you can turn into typed values once.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;A familiar entry point for ASP.NET, Workers, and other DI-driven runtimes.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;A bridge from dynamic host registrations to typed, honest core logic.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;pragmatic-access-flowinject&#34;&gt;Pragmatic Access: &lt;code&gt;Flow.inject&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;code&gt;Flow.inject&amp;lt;&#39;T&amp;gt;()&lt;/code&gt; pulls a service directly from the &lt;code&gt;IServiceProvider&lt;/code&gt; in the environment.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;background-color:#f8f8f8;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-fsharp&#34; data-lang=&#34;fsharp&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#204a87;font-weight:bold&#34;&gt;let&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#000&#34;&gt;handleRequest&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ce5c00;font-weight:bold&#34;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#000&#34;&gt;flow&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ce5c00;font-weight:bold&#34;&gt;{&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;    &lt;span style=&#34;color:#204a87;font-weight:bold&#34;&gt;let!&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#000&#34;&gt;db&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ce5c00;font-weight:bold&#34;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#000&#34;&gt;Flow&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#000;font-weight:bold&#34;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#000&#34;&gt;inject&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ce5c00;font-weight:bold&#34;&gt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#000&#34;&gt;MyDbContext&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ce5c00;font-weight:bold&#34;&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ce5c00;font-weight:bold&#34;&gt;_,&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ce5c00;font-weight:bold&#34;&gt;_&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#3465a4&#34;&gt;()&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;    &lt;span style=&#34;color:#204a87;font-weight:bold&#34;&gt;let!&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#000&#34;&gt;api&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ce5c00;font-weight:bold&#34;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#000&#34;&gt;Flow&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#000;font-weight:bold&#34;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#000&#34;&gt;inject&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ce5c00;font-weight:bold&#34;&gt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#000&#34;&gt;IExternalApi&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ce5c00;font-weight:bold&#34;&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ce5c00;font-weight:bold&#34;&gt;_,&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ce5c00;font-weight:bold&#34;&gt;_&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#3465a4&#34;&gt;()&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;    &lt;span style=&#34;color:#8f5902;font-style:italic&#34;&gt;// ...&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ce5c00;font-weight:bold&#34;&gt;}&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;This is the most ergonomic way to use FsFlow inside existing .NET applications.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
